Patient: What exercise can I do for my heart condition?
Educator: Walking is safe and easy. Start with 10 minutes daily, then slowly increase.

Patient: But my neighborhood isn't safe.
Educator: You can walk inside your home or try marching in place.

Patient: I can't afford gym membership, what can I do?
Educator: No worries, try body-weight exercises like squats, lunges, or push-ups at home.

Patient: I'm old, will these exercises be too hard?
Educator: Start slow and listen to your body. If you feel discomfort, stop. 

Patient: Can I also do some stretching?
Educator: Absolutely, gentle stretching can be very beneficial. Just be careful not to overstretch.